preference.name: CATIA_loader_bl_attr_list_of_struct_table
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns displayed in the Structure table in left-to-right order. Possible values are real name of Bom line attribute and following keywords: - NONE: Do not display default columns - cat2_has_dst : display the "CAD - CAD dataset found" column which would contain true value if the current element has a primary cad dataset, otherwise false value - cat2_is_co : display the "IsCO - dataset / bvr CO status" column which could have 3 possible states check-in / check-out / check-out by other - cat2_has_mml : display the "MML - Is source / target of MML / MMLAssy links" column which would contain true value if the current element is a source / target of a mml or mmlassy link, otherwise false value - cat2_has_dwg : display the "DWG - Is pointed by a drawing" column which would contain true value if the current element is pointed by a drawing link, otherwise false value - cat2_has_mfg : display the "MFG - Is pointed by a manufacturing" column which would contain true value if the current element is pointed by a manufacturing link, otherwise false value - cat2_has_anal: display the "ANAL - Is pointed by an analysis" column which would contain true value if the current element is pointed by an analysis link, otherwise false value - cat2_has_ehf: display the "EHF - Is pointed by a flattening link" column which would contain true value if the current element is pointed by an flattening link, otherwise false value - cat2_has_gde: display the "Has Laminate Bomline" column which would contain true value if the current element has GDE Bomlines, otherwise false value
